column5: My thoughts will be with you and your family throughout the week Wayne. We'll talk again soon.
Thanks.. truck is running off we go.

Condolences to you and your family Wayne.  Good for you for spending time on the water with your mom and her catching that Laker...her smiling with you and the fish is heartwarming and I'm sure will be proudly displayed in your home.  Take care, Tony

Wayne, My sincerest condolences on the loss of your mother. It has been a rough year for you but hang in there. My thoughts and prayers are with you and your family during this difficult time. Take care of yourself and your family.
Condolences to you and yours Wayne,from all of us here....TC and tight lines......Chuck.....
Sincere condolences, may the memories help you overcome your familes loss.
Sorry to hear of your loss, I hope you find solice in the memories and relive them often.
my sincerest condolences wayne, this has to have been one tough summer
So sorry, Wayne. Best to you and your family.  Mike
Not a summer to remember Wayne.  My deepest sympathies for your Mom and your late sister.

THANKS to everyone for your condolences, thoughts and beautiful flowers......and thanks to the few silly nuts that made the trip for the funeral. The world's still a pretty good place afterall !  Wayne
Very sorry to hear about your Mom's passing Wayne.  My condolences.  Craig
So sorry to hear of your loss Wayne. Cherish those memories.............  Sincere condolences my friend, John & Barbara
Sorry to hear Irish.  Respects and Condolences to you and yours.  Nemo
Wow, that is ALOT to go through Wayne in a short period of time.  Sorry to hear once again for your loss and hang in there.
Our family is thinking of ya Wayne..  our condolences.  A tough summer for sure.
Our deepest sympathies Wayne and family, be well.
My condolences Wayne....  Chris
Me and my boys are thinking of you. Our deepest condolences to you and your family.
Very sorry for the loss Irish.  Those are beautiful pictures though, cherish the memories!  Jason
Sorry for the Loss Wayne  my condolences...  it's been a hard year for your Family
Our condolences Wayne, to you and your family.  Dan
My condolences to you and your family!
My condolences Wayne.
Sorry to hear.  Tough summer for sure.   Cheers.  K
My condolences to you and your family through your toughest times.  Keep the memories strong and life will live on forever.
My condolences Wayne.
sorry to hear about your loss wayne
My condolences.
Wayne.... Man you have had it tough this year.... damn...  I feel for you and you're family...  Please accept my condolences.  G.
Wayne, I am very sorry to hear of your Mothers passing, It looks like you have shared many wonder times together and I am sure you have many ,many great memories of her to draw on! Condolences, Ryan
Sorry for your loss Wayne  My sincere condolences to you and your family.  Hang in there bud
Thanks for your thoughts everyone ! We're out the door shortly...
Sincere condolences!!!!
sincerest condolences Wayne...take care
Sorry for your loss Wayne. It's the hardest thing losing a parent.
Sincerest condolences Wayne.  Keep your chin up, bud.  S.
Sorry for your loss Wayne.

Sorry for your loss Wayne.  Sincerely, Splashhopper and Botbot  here is a prayer that i am often time reminded to use in times of loss or stress:  Prayer of Saint Francis of Assisi  Lord, make me an instrument of your peace. Where there is hatred, let me sow love; where there is injury,pardon; where there is doubt, faith; where there is despair, hope; where there is darkness, light; and where there is sadness, joy.   O Divine Master, grant that I may not so much seek to be consoled as to console; to be understood as to understand; to be loved as to love. For it is in giving that we receive; it is in pardoning that we are pardoned; and it is in dying that we are born to eternal life. Amen
my condolences and heartfelt sympathies.
So sorry about your loss Wayne, please accept our heartfelt condolences.  Jack and Jackie
My condolences to you and your family.
So sorry for your loss.  Condolences to you and your family.
It's a good thing you inherited your Mom's strong spirit, Wayne, you've most certainly needed it this summer. Stay strong bud, & my deepest condolances.
That was a great post bud, in spite of all this turmoil...  My deepest sympathies.  Let's hope the fall is better on ya.
my condolences and heartfelt sympathies.  Geoff
Sorry for your loss My deepest condolences to you and your family Dan
It's a terrible thing. I'm sure she was a great woman.
my thoughts and prayers are with you and your family.

I'm very sorry to hear of your mother passing. It has been a tough summer for you and your family. My heart goes out for all, remember those good memories as the ones you have shared with us in the photos. Peace be with her.
I am so very sorry for your loss Wayne!
My condolences Wayne to your family, it's been a tough summer for you...  Maureen
My condolences. Sorry to hear about your losses this year. That is tough.
My condolences Wayne....keep your chin up through these tough times.  Jason
Very sorry to hear the loss of your mother. My condolences to you and your family Wayne.
Sorry for your loss Wayne... you have had a pretty tough year. Please pass on my heartfelt sympathies to your family. HH
Sorry to hear Wayne.
Sincerest condolences Wayne Will see you sat. Hang in there bud!!!
My condolences Wayne,  She looks like a vibrant woman who had a good life.  Take care
my condolences to you adn your family
We are very sorry to hear of your loss Wayne...  Moms are so very special it is hard to take their loss but they are forever in our hearts...We know ours are...  Maribeth and Beans

Some happy shots taken on July 8th, 3 hours before I had to tell her that her daughter was dead.  Saturday morning my Mother's aortic aneurysm blew in her sleep. We knew it was a ticking time bomb... but the last months turmoil sure helped take it's toll. I have peace with the fact that I flew down to Smiths Falls and saw her in good spirits on Friday, for about 4 hours, before skirting weather back to the lake just shy of darkness.  I'll miss you Mom and I'm sure I glad that you caught your first Lake Trout (that was bigger than Linda's ! lol)  Wayne   Visitation for Dorothy O'Shea Welz - Friday Aug 28th, 2-4 and 7-9pm at Lannin's Funeral Home, Main St. Smiths Falls, Ontario  Funeral Saturday Aug 29th, 2PM, at Westminster Presbyterian Church, 11 Church St W, Smiths Falls, Ontario  In lieu of flowers donations to the Trinity United Church Restoration Fund, the Crohn's and Colitis Foundation of Canada, the Canadian Cancer Society or the Heart and Stroke Foundation of Canada would be greatly appeciated by the family.  On-line condolences available at http://lannin.ca/
Sorry for your Loss Wayne, you've had a tough summer, our thoughts are with your family at this time.
Wayne you've had quite a summer, condolences to you and yours.
Not the report I was looking forward to friend.  Sorry of her of passing. Both Betty and I send our prayers and thoughts with you and your family tonight.
Wayne, those pictures are beautiful! Sorry for your loss, but your Mom looked liked she was having a great time fishing with you.
My condolences Wayne.
Wayne, my deepest condolences. It's hard to lose a parent or any family member, but the memories will last for ever. Take care  A
Deepest condolences Wayne, boy its been a helluva summer for you.  Nice pics, and a wonderful smile I am sure you will treasure those - especially the one of you holding her fish for her

Sorry to hear more bad news from you Wayne, it certainly has been quite the summer for you.  Your Mom looks like she was having the time of her life that day, living life to the fullest.  Memories to last for ever.  My deepest condolences to you and your family.

you have had a lot to bare  this summer sorry for your loss I still remember the picture of her riding on the water tube the other year, you must have great memories of her, that you will have for ever  hang in there
Sorry to hear! Memories last forever, make sure you are as memorable as she is!!
Sorry to hear the bad news Wayne.... My deepest condolences to you and your family Leechman
Enjoy the memories Wayne, and you will always smile.  Rob
The pics of your mother tubing behind your boat a couple of years ago shows her strength of spirit. Take care and try for muskies this fall, that will sooth your soul.
Wayne, I'm so sorry to hear this, one hell of a summer for you for sure.  My condolences.  Jim
Patsy and I send along our condolences in your lost.  I know it's been a tough year for you Wayne, but hang tough bud.  Hang tough.

My deepest, deepest condolences to you and Leah Wayne. I remember reading your posts about getting your mom out fishing with the family. As I just lost my Mom Dec. 30th, 2008, I can sympathize. Cherish all the time you had with her.  MOM'S ARE THE BEST, and they will truly be missed. They leave a hole in our lives that cannot be refilled.
My condolences as well. You have had a difficult summer, I can only try to empathize with what you have been enduring.
Wayne, So sorry to hear of your loss again for the second time this summer. Man, you hang in there. I know it must be tough.  You have my deepest condolences.  Brian
My condolences Wayne.  Enjoy the memories   Dan
Sorry to hear this Wayne I too have lost my mother and its a hard thing to go through. My best to you and yours.
My condolences to you and your family.
Definitely a tough summer, Wayne...we are all thinking of you and yours.

Wayne, I have missed your posts all summer. I am sorry to hear of your mother as I was your sister. There are many of us that are approaching that time in our life where we have to start saying goodbye to folks. Think nice thoughts. Jim
Sorry for your loss My deepest condolences to you and your family  Rick
